      "algorithmDeviationCount": "Algorithm deviations"
    }
  },
  "teachingPoints": [
    "Septic shock rewards parallel work: access, monitoring, cultures, lactate, fluids, antibiotics, and pressor preparation can overlap.",
    "Cultures matter, but antibiotics should not be delayed when the patient is crashing.",
    "Persistent hypotension after initial fluids should trigger vasopressor support rather than endless fluid cycling.",
    "The case is not complete until perfusion is reassessed and disposition is moving."
  ]
}
